(flag) matrix[curL][curR] = ‘#’; break; case ‘s’: curL ++; if (flag) matrix[curL][curR] = ‘#’; break; case ‘a’: curR –; if (flag) matrix[curL][curR] = ‘#’; break; case ‘d’: curR ++; if (flag) matrix[curL][curR] = ‘#’; break; case ‘e’: if (flag) flag = 0; else flag = 1; break; default: printf(“unknow err [%c]\n”, ch); break; } } fclose(fpIn); fpOut = fopen(“2.txt”, “w”); if (fpOut == NULL) { printf(“open 2.txt err\n”); return 0; } for (i = 0; i < ROW; i ++) { for (j =0; j < COL; j++) { fprintf(fpOut, "%c", matrix[i][j]); } fprintf(fpOut, "%s", "\n"); } fclose(fpOut); return 0; } TSL
